From: ws@xivic.bo.open.de (Wolfgang Schelongowski)
Subject: Re: Which UART for fast (14.4) modem?
Date: Thu, 14 Oct 93 11:52:23 MEST

gast@cs.ucla.edu writes:

> Is a 16550 UART recommended or is it not needed?

A 14.4 Modem will usually need to communicate with the UART of
the PC with at least 19200 bits/sec, better are 38400. If you don't
have a FIFO in the UART, that means an interrupt every 500 or even
250 us. If you don't serve it in time, you lose characters and
have to ask the other side to retransmit ===> your throughput goes
to zero, and your telephone company will get rich.

So you need an UART with FIFO eg. 16550A/AF/AFN. The 16550s without
A are IMHO early models where the FIFO doesn't really work.

--
Wolfgang Schelongowski  ws@xivic.bo.open.de
