From: ws@xivic.bo.open.de (Wolfgang Schelongowski)
Subject: Re: Linux count: HELP with countries of domains
Date: Thu, 14 Oct 93 12:11:48 MEST

hta@uninett.no (Harald T. Alvestrand) wrote:

> The greatest number of comments to the Linux count has been on my
> allocation of domains to countries.
> (The count is now 2928 users)
>
> So, I did some homework, and now have the following configuration
> file for mapping domains to countries:
>
> # Mapping file for domain -> country
> # Each line is a country + domains that map to this country
> # More than one line per country can exist
> de: sub.org germany.eu.net xlink.net
...
> Any comments/corrections to these mappings are appreciated!

When I see this, and further comments, I believe you should _not_
have done any homework (however nice it was from you to do it),
because the usenet addresses seem to be far too irregular for you
to ever succeed in a sensible amount of time.

My suggestion: Let anybody who wants to be registerred for a
country add an _optional_ [countrycode] somewhere to the subject.

While you're at it, you might consider adding +n to the voting
which means "I know n people who use Linux but can not mail you".
The count of these must be kept separate and will contain duplicates.

So e.g. somebody from sub.org who knows 5 other people who use
Linux but can not e-mail to you would write:

Subject: [de] I use linux at home +5

All these additions should be optional and may be put either at the
beginning or the end, of course.

--
Wolfgang Schelongowski  ws@xivic.bo.open.de
